27/10/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Defence Minister Vlado Buckovski and Army Chief of Staff General Metodi Stamboliski left Sunday (26 October) on a two-day visit to Iraq. They will meet with Macedonia's contingent in the international peacekeeping mission there, as well as with the international command and the new civil administration. In June, Macedonia sent 31 peacekeepers to Iraq.
In other news, defence ministry spokesman Marjan Gjurovski announced Friday that the government will present the country's Membership Action Plan to NATO member states in Brussels on 4 November. The plan would outline progress in preparations for NATO membership over the past year, as well as details of the new strategy for security and defence. (MIA, Makfax - 26/10/03; A1 TV - 24/10/03)
